            </br>
            <p class="header">FAQ</p>
            <p>
                <i>What is the story behind your object?</i></br></br>

                TODO: image

                </br></br>
                
                <i>Where does it come from?</i></br></br>

                From a place called earth out of an artistic human mind.
                </br></br>

                <i>Why does it exist?</i></br></br>

                The purpose of this object is to create an interactive and decorative object allowing the users to explore the magnetism through visually appealing playfulness with a ferrofluid container of any kind placed on top of the display.
                </br></br>

                <i>What is the personality of your object?</i></br></br>

                It has a simplistic, complex and yet artsy display. One can understand its nature by exploring the circuits path behind a transparent wall.
                </br></br>

                <i>How does its personality manifest itself in the physical world?</i></br></br>

                It manifests it by captivating a visitor by the sci-fi like dark liquid reacting to hand gestures.
                </br></br>

                <i>What makes your object do what it does?</i></br></br>

                There is no need for a direct interaction for this object to display the 3D magnetic field force using the ferrofluid. By default, one can observe them and with a simple hand gesture not requiring much of an effort, this person can make it move according to its interests.
                </br></br>

                <i>Is the personality of your object related to its physical manifestation?</i></br></br>

                Its personnality is related to its physical manifestation by its core reason of existance : binding Art with Science by intriguing and facinating the end user.
                </br></br>

                <i>What emotions does your object evoke/provoke?</i></br></br>

                Facination, uncertainty and feeling of magic.
                </br></br>

                <i>Are they the same for everyone?</i></br></br>

                They may vary according to people's knowledge of the ferrofluid. However, even one that knows the essence of this liquid, would still be interested into seeing and now even controlling its magnetic field using the movement sensor.
                </br></br>
            </p>
            </br>
